{
  "text": "Multivoxel pattern-based mapping [CITATION_1] was carried out to localize cortical regions responding with linearly discriminable patterns to different facial identities. To this end, we separately computed at each location within a cortical mask the discriminability of every pair of identities using linear SVM classification and leave-one-run-out cross-validation (Methods and SI). The resulting information-based map of each participant was normalized to a common space and analyzed at the group level to assess the presence of identity-related information and its approximate spatial location.",
